      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLOOD WARNING (8) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where he gave a sight, finishing third (17.43) and beaten 1.5 lengths over 300m at this track. Good form should continue. BLUEY BRANN (2) turned in a better effort at Cannington last start, finishing second behind Penny Pincher (16.22) in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to be in this for a long way. SWEETIE PIE (4) has shown good improvement at her last two starts, hitting the frame latest when 3rd at this track over 300m. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Will give a great sight again. ZATARA MAC (3) can sneak into the finish.",
